Edited January 25, 2020 by tonimark

The problem is unchanged. Some of your mods are not compatible with KSP 1.8

BDArmory / AdjustableLandingGear  is probably causing the hang on load: 

[ModuleManager] Intercepted a ReflectionTypeLoadException. List of broken DLLs:
BDAnimationModules 0.0.0.0 GameData\BahaSP\Plugins\BDAnimationModules.dll

You'll also have trouble with AirplanePlus parts as some of the textures were in DXT3 format and could not be loaded. Some shader errors at the at seem to be caused by "JSIExternalCameraSelector", possibly not updated to the new "legacy" shader names.
what legancy ? , if you asked me i updated airplane plus , bd armory and reinstalled jsi , does rpm mod is too old to be loaded (incompatable with 1.8) ?

I’ve updated RPM for 1.8 here, but the camera selector crash won’t be fixed until the next release (v0.31.1)

BDAnimationModules is a separate mod, probably installed as a dependency from something else.  And each time you change something you should post a new log file so we can see if it’s the same problem or a new one.
I am having the same issue.  Not even sure what mod installs BDAnimationModules.dll.  CKAN, at least on a mac, does not show what mods depend on a given mod.
